{
  "stem": "11133.2",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Quite often.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You know, he took great pleasure frightening people, so he would enjoy walking through the camp with his two huge Great Danes, and he-- he got enormous pleasure out of putting fear into people.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There was just-- he was a very evil man.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I also distinctly remember one day, he came to Madritsch, spoke to my father, and all of a sudden we saw my father walking with him down the road.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Well, it was incredible fear, because we didn't know that my father was going to return, you know?",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But he did-- he did come back.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I don't know what it was all about.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But you see, Goeth was-- Madritsch was friendly with Goeth, just as Schindler was friendly with Goeth, in a sense that they were supplying Goeth with all kinds of goodies, you know.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That's how, you know, the bribery worked.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And so we had a certain amount of protection, as long as we worked for Madritsch.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Madritsch was a wonderful person-- he and his companion, Mr.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Titsch.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They were really classy-- two people who somehow just got caught.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "You know, there were a lot of Germans and Austrians who were caught in the situation, not of their doing, really, and they did the best they could.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They did bring in food for us.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Madritsch brought in loads of-- loaves of bread for the people-- for his workers-- and medications.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They were very decent people.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I worked at the Madritsch factory till the concentration camp closed-- which was, I believe-- now I have a hard time remembering whether it was September that the camp actually closed, and we were all shipped to Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 38
    }
  ],
